      "file_path": "openecomp-be/lib/openecomp-tosca-lib/src/main/java/org/openecomp/sdc/tosca/services/impl/ToscaAnalyzerServiceImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 591,
      "message": "Same pattern. You don't need this local variable. It is very easy to get it wrong with re-assignments. Compare:\n\nboolean findFlatEntity(List<Map<String, Import>> imports) {\n    for (Map<String, Import> importMap : imports) {\n\n        if (isFlatEntity(importMap, entity, serviceTemplate, filesScanned, toscaModel,elementType,typeId);\n            return true;\n    }\n\n    return false;\n}\n\nIt can be even more concise with Java 8 functional style.",
